      <section eId="sec_3610">
        <num>3610</num>
        <heading>State and towns not liable on corporation bonds</heading>
        <subsection eId="sec_3610__subsec_a">
          <num>(a)</num>
          <content>
            <p>The state\nshall not be liable on the bonds or notes of the corporation and such\nbonds or notes shall not be a debt of the state, and such bonds and\nnotes shall contain on the face thereof a statement to such effect.\n</p>
          </content>
        </subsection>
        <subsection eId="sec_3610__subsec_b">
          <num>(b)</num>
          <content>
            <p>Except as may be authorized by the town pursuant to section seven\nof article seventeen of the state constitution and section thirty-six\nhundred eight of this title, the town shall not be liable on the bonds\nor notes of the corporation and such bonds or notes shall not be a debt\nof the town, and such bonds and notes shall contain on the face thereof\na statement to such effect or a statement describing the town liability\nthereon, if any.\n</p>
          </content>
        </subsection>
      </section>
